headline: AZO Q3 Deep Dive: Store Expansion, Tariff Pressures, and Margin Outlook Shape Results
summary: Auto parts and accessories retailer AutoZone (NYSE:AZO) met Wall Street’s revenue expectations in Q3 CY2025, but sales were flat year on year at $6.24 billion. Its non-GAAP profit of $48.71 per share was 4% below analysts’ consensus estimates.
